Package: autoscroll
Architecture: linux-any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: system-wide Windows-style middle-click autoscroll for Linux
 autoscroll provides system-wide middle-click autoscroll (like Windows)
 for Linux. It works on X11 and all Wayland compositors (GNOME, KDE,
 cosmic-comp, Sway, Hyprland, Gamescope, Weston).
 .
 The daemon uses evdev+uinput with zero runtime dependencies.
 Quick press+release of the middle button passes through as paste.
